## 2. Borrowing

Instead of moving ownership, you can borrow with references:

```rust
let s1 = String::from("hello");
let len = calculate_length(&s1);
println!("{} has length {}", s1, len);
```

The `&` creates a reference. References are immutable by default.

## 3. Mutable References

```rust
let mut s = String::from("hello");
change(&mut s);
```

Only one mutable reference at a time. This prevents data races at compile time.
